t: And*p the angel that talked with me came again, and waked me, as a man that is wakened out of his sleep,

And*p said unto me, What seest thou? And I said, I have looked, and behold a candlestick all of gold, with a bowl upon the top of it, and his seven lamps thereon, and seven pipes to the seven lamps, which are upon the top thereof:
And*p two olive trees by it, one upon the right side of the bowl, and the other upon the left side thereof.
So*p I answered and spake to the angel that talked with me, saying, What are these, my lord?
Then*p the angel that talked with me answered and said unto me, Knowest thou not what these be? And I said, No, my lord.
Then*p he answered and spake unto me, saying, This is the word of the Lord*s unto Zerubbabel, saying, Not by might, nor by power, but by my spirit, saith the Lord*s of hosts.
Who*p art thou, O great mountain? before Zerubbabel thou shalt become a plain: and he shall bring forth the headstone thereof with shoutings, crying, Grace, grace unto it.
Moreover*p the word of the Lord*s came unto me, saying,
The*p hands of Zerubbabel have laid the foundation of this house; his hands shall also finish it; and thou shalt know that the Lord*s of hosts hath sent me unto you.

For*p who hath despised the day of small things? for they shall rejoice, and shall see the plummet in the hand of Zerubbabel with those seven; they are the eyes of the Lord,*s which run to and fro through the whole earth.
Then*p answered I, and said unto him, What are these two olive trees upon the right side of the candlestick and upon the left side thereof?
And*p I answered again, and said unto him, What be these two olive branches which through the two golden pipes empty the golden oil out of themselves?
And*p he answered me and said, Knowest thou not what these be? And I said, No, my lord.
Then*p said he, These are the two anointed ones, that stand by the Lord of the whole earth.
